VII. To recapitulate.

(1) The terms ‘colonia’ ‘municipium' ‘praefectura’ were not, perhaps, mutually exclusive.

(1) A majority-perhaps all-ol the ‘municipia’ and ‘coloniae civium Romanorum’ ol the earlier period (ie. ol that which ended in the year 90 nc.) were also ‘praefecturae’ and some oi them retained the latter title in Cicero's time.

(3) The term ‘municipium' and no 111111, applied iu Cicero's time to such old Latin aud other allied communities in Italy as had received the lull Roman franchise in sc. 90, or later; and perhaps when Cicero speaks ol ‘coloniae,' ‘municipia' and ‘praefecturae' he uses the term ‘municipium’ in this narrower sense.
